HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1302
By Boyd
A RESOLUTION to honor Gwyn Jennings on the occasion of her
retirement from teaching.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in paying tribute
to a professional educator who has devoted her life to classroom instruction, always maintaining
a nurturing, disciplined, and joyful culture of learning for her students; and
WHEREAS, Gwyn Jennings has taught at Coles Ferry Elementary School in the
Lebanon Special School District for her entire thirty-four-year career, serving as a first grade
teacher for twenty years before becoming the school's technology instructor; and
WHEREAS, as a first grade teacher, Ms. Jennings designed and implemented a
comprehensive literacy program that was focused on early intervention and diagnostic
assessment; she also tutored students in reading for many years, continuing this practice after
she transitioned to her new position; and
WHEREAS, for the past fourteen years, Ms. Jennings has been responsible for the
school-wide technology curriculum for grades K-5, and in this role, she has ensured that digital
literacy is always balanced with academic rigor and that technology serves as a tool for
creativity and problem-solving; and
WHEREAS, she has also served as Cole Ferry's social media coordinator and produced
a student television show, "CFE tv"; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Jennings's excellence as an instructor and classroom leader has been
duly recognized; she has been twice honored as Teacher of the Year at Coles Ferry (2007 and
2021), and she was selected District Teacher of the Year in 2007; and
HJR1302
017379
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Gwyn Jennings is also renowned for her leadership among her peers; she
has diligently mentored many young teachers through peer professional development and
student-teacher coaching; and
WHEREAS, a devout Christian, Ms. Jennings helped found the Fellowship of Christian
Athletes program at Coles Ferry; she practices her faith at Rural Hill Church of Christ, where
she serves as children's education curriculum coordinator and teacher; and
WHEREAS, this exemplary educator earned her Bachelor of Science degree in
Education from Tennessee Technological University and a Master of Science degree in
Reading from Middle Tennessee State University; and
WHEREAS, Gwyn Jennings is retiring from her duties at the end of the school year; we
acknowledge that although her teaching position will be filled, she can never truly be replaced;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor Gwyn Jennings on the occasion of her retirement from teaching,
salute her thirty-four years spent nurturing the growth of young minds at Coles Ferry Elementary
School, and extend to her our best wishes for a happy and fulfilling retirement.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
